transcript.text: Hello, welcome to on Print Shop Designer Studio tutorial series.
In today's video we will be talking about the dependency rules and how you can create them.
You can create dependency rules for the PDF block templates.
With the dependency rules, you can show or hide the other block by creating some rules or conditions.
In addition, you can put some predefined values of blocks by applying some conditions.
So let's get started.
To give you an idea about the features, let's first see a scenario from the Designer studio.
So on the front end, when any customer selects a PDF block template for personalization in the designer studio, they will have these blocks and settings to manage.

For example, if the customer doesn't want to add their phone number in the design and leaves the value against the phone number blank, then the value will disappear, but the text block on the phone will still be there.
To overcome such scenarios, we have the Dependency Rules feature.
Now let's see how you can create one.
In the admin panel, navigate to the Templates section and click on the PDF Block Templates.
Select one template from the PDF block template listing that you want to create dependency rules.
Click on the Action button and select Manage Blocks.
You can see and verify the blocks added to the template in the Manage Blocks section.
As you can see, for Phone Number, Text and value there are different blocks.
Now move to the Dependency Rules tab to create a rule for hiding the phone number text block.
Click on the Add button.
Give a title to a rule such as the Phone Number rule.
Enable the status as Active and then select the type of rule.
If the end type is selected then the below action will be taken into consideration only when all terms are fulfilled.
And if the OR type is selected then the below action will be taken when any one of the terms is true.
These two sections are like.
If these terms match then the configured actions will be taken.
So in if you can find the list of all the blocks, select the phone P number and then in the operator of the condition drop down.
You have various conditions to select from.
But in this scenario, let us select is empty.
Now in the below section from the Do drop down, select Hide and in blocks select the phone P which is the phone number text block.
Let's save the rule.
Now go to the front end again to see how this is applied to the template.
Just refresh or reload the page and remove the phone number from the space.
Now you can see that the phone number text gets hidden and the below blocks move upward to fill the space.
Please note that the blocks below the phone move upward depending on the alignment rules, which we have covered in another video.
So this is how you can create multiple dependency rules in the PDF block templates.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
